CBRE is pleased to present Little Zak’s Academy, Artarmon, a prime three level child care investment in a core employment hub within Sydney’s North Shore. 

6 Clarendon Street, Artarmon is currently leased to Affinity Education Group, who own and operate 167 childcare centres nationally. Trading as Little Zak’s Academy Artarmon, the premium childcare provider offers a secure lease with options until 2052.

Little Zak's Artarmon benefits from the following key attributes:

• Net Income: $1,260,000 p.a.
• Brand new triple net 10-year lease to leading childcare provider Affinity Education Group with options to 2052
• Fixed annual 3.5% rental increases
• Childcare operating with approval for 210 places
• Modern fit out with depreciation benefits
• Well performing growth suburb with a thriving child care market
• Total building NLA: 3,222sqm*
• Located in the Artarmon employment hub within 1.1km* of the St Leonards Train Station and Artarmon Train Station

The property is to be offered by way of expressions of interest closing Wednesday, 06 December 2017 at 4 PM (AEST).

*Approximate

CBRE as exclusive agents are pleased to offer 555 Pacific Highway, Artarmon to market for sale via Expressions of Interest closing on Thursday 16th July 2020 at 3pm (AEST).

This property represents a prime investment opportunity with significant land holding in Sydney’s tightly held Lower North Shore. 

Tenanted by North Shore Ford, Australia’s second largest Ford retailer and part of the Peter Warren Automotive Group on a triple net lease, this property is a highly desirable addition to any investor’s portfolio.

Key attributes include:
•	Rare Large Corner Position Land Parcel of 2,535sqm* in Sydney’s tightly held Lower North Shore
•	Tenanted by North Shore Ford, the second largest Ford retailer in Australia
•	Ultra-wide 83 metres* street frontage on Pacific Highway with high exposure
•	Net Passing Income of $797,810.62 plus GST per annum*
•	Secured long lease till 2026 plus 3 years option
•	600 metres* to Artarmon Train Station and Shops

•	Set to Benefit from the proposed Draft Chatswood CBD Strategy and Draft Local Centre Strategy 2036 proposals by Willoughby Council
